Important:
1. Import speedup for gene annotation initialization on MySQL Databases
3. Export TSV tables for pheno, feature, expression, DGE tables
  roger get-expression-matrix GEO1234 --outfile /my/out/file
  roger get-dge-result used_contrast used_design GEO1234
  roger show-pheno-matrix    # prints (except) to display
4. Convenience methods for defining / importing design & contrast matrices:
  roger add-design --use-pheno-column "SAMPLE_GROUP" --group-levels # or --group-levels-file
  roger add-contrast --make-contrasts='["CmpDX": "Threat23", "Bla": "Blub"]'
2. Add update utility for matrix data, e.g.:
  roger update-pheno         # Reload pheno data from PhenoSrc field
  roger update-pheno --file /new/pheno/data.tsv
3. Quality checking for gene annotation import:
   When importing genes, try to filter out potential "junk genes", e.g. Don't include ensembl identifiers that point to unmapped chromosome region

Backlog:
